criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. SBP＜90 mm Hg or MAP ＜70 mm Hg or SBP decrease ＞40mmHg or need vasoactive drugs;

          2. Skin that is cold and clammy, capillary refill time ＞4.5s, urine output of
             ＜0.5ml/Kg.hr and lactate＞2mmol/L;

          3. SHOCK presented within 6 hr.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. ＜18 years old;

          2. Pregnancy;

          3. Patient or family member refuse to be enrolled.
